   <font class="ArticleSource"><big>Test Server:</big></font>

   <font class="ArticleHead"><big>Testing...1..2..3</big></font>

   <font class="ArticleAuthorLight">&nbsp;filed by </font><font class="ArticleAuthor">Kohath</font>

   <div align="right">
   <font class="ArticleTime">03/14/2002 12:32 PM CST</font>
   <div align="left">
   <font class="ArticleText">This morning saw many changes appear on Test Server--changes that will bring much-needed help to people at all stages of the game. Let's dig in...<p><big>Buff You, Buddy!</big><p>According to <a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/">Casters Realm</a>, there's a new <B>/rtarget</b> command to target the last person who gave you a /tell. Buffers and translocaters alike will apprecite this added convenience. Is it groundbreaking? No, but every little bit helps, especially in raid situations.<p><big>Dead Noobs, Dead Noobs, What'cha Gonna Do?</big><p>Also on the test server is the fact that level 10 or below characters are now so inconsequential that they no longer even leave a corpse when they die.  Dead noobs simply teleport to their bind point with all their equipment intact.<p>This is good for noobs, but I'd suggest making it only apply through level 5 or 6.  At some point, a new EQ player needs to learn how to do corpse recovery, and it would be best to learn this before you have lots of expensive equipment to lose.<p>This change, when combined with the new level 14 revive spell, will make corpse runs increasingly rare. It might also provide a safe method of teleportation for the enterprising low-level player.<p>On the other hand, without dead noobs, what are the lions in the Commonlands going to eat? Verant really needs to think about the ecology of Norrath.<p><big>Watch Your Step</big><p>Halflings and Gnomes can be hybrids now on test.  Expect to see a lot of short, pointy lowbies in your near future.  At least they won't litter the ground with corpses for a while.    <p>This change has all kinds of roleplay implications. Lots of <a href="http://forums.interealms.com/shadowknight/showthread.php?s=6f239c0df3d35362cd568c9bee218289&amp;threadid=13115">shadowknights</a>, <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessage?topicID=14844.topic">paladins</a>, and <a href="http://forums.interealms.com/ranger/showthread.php?s=a26376b47d9d8f19e49187085228b8e9&amp;threadid=38613">rangers</a> have mixed feelings about the whole thing, saying it's too late in the game to add new race/class combos. Uh, hello... Iksar monks, anyone? I bet Moorgard will be twinking a gnome SK, gnome pally, and halfling ranger, just out of spite.<p><big>Raid Channels</big><p>You've been asking for this feature for <b>years</b>.  It's always been <i>something we'd like to implement when we have the time</i>.<p>Well, now it's here.  I logged into Test server this morning, and there's now a /join command that allows you to join one or more private chat channels.  Channels can even have a password, which will help keep <a href="http://www.legacyofsteel.net/index.shtml">Stalkers, Wanna-be's, and Unoriginal Bastards</a> from interrupting your witty raiding banter.<p>This is an outstanding development.  Thanks, Verant!<p><big>Too Good to be True?</big><p>The best of the new additions is the one that's only a rumor.    For obvious reasons, I wasn't able to test this when I logged into the Test server.  But the guys at <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showMessage?topicID=10258.topic">the Safehouse</a> are reporting that pre-50 hell levels are gone.<p>This is too good to be true.  I'm expecting Alan to announce this afternoon that this isn't the case.  If it <b>is</b> true, then this is by far the most important development since the release of Luclin.<p>I certainly hope this one comes true, but math has a way of resisting even it's strongest-willed opponents.<p><b>Update 8:15 CST:</b> Scott Hartsman <a href="http://necro.eqclasses.com/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=1453">posted on the necro board</a>:<p><i>&quot;If we did make a change like this, we'd have to find a way for it not to cause side effects to people's current exp.&quot;</i><p>Instant analysis of this is that it lends a small amount of credibility to the rumor.  Mr. Hartsman's posts tend to be direct, and his post lacks a denial of the rumor.  Maybe he's tired though.<p><big>Tommorrow on Test</big><p>What are we going to see tomorrow on Test?  More than anything I'd like to see the new interface and the Bazaar. We'll see.<br></font>
  </td>
 </tr>
